<center><table border=0><tr><td><center><H2><font face=arial>Monks Need ....</font></H2></center>
<font face=arial size=2><b>Posted By:</b> <A HREF="/cgi-local/whois.cgi?Zyphan">Zyphan</a><br>
<b>Posted On:</b> 9:12 p.m. 30/4/1999<br>
<b>Subject:</b> Monks Need ....<p>
<br><center><img src="http://www.everworld.net/images/datel.gif" width=46 height=22 border=0><img src="http://www.everworld.net/images/dateblnk.gif" width=100 height=22 border=0><img src="http://www.everworld.net/images/dater.gif" width=306 height=22 border=0></center><BR></STRONG><FONT SIZE=2 color=#F4D99F FACE=arial>
<P>Why do monks get Riposte so late? they are martial artists, so by nature they should be able to counter attack much sooner.... and here's a thought if warriors get Berserk when they are 35% life, why doesn't a monk get like a calming skill? if they are in tone with mind and body they shouldn't feel a great deal of pain...so they agility wont go down, it just wont rise? monks should also get meditate to heal faster maybe at a higher level but they should have it nonetheless...

<BR>
</FONT></td></tr></table></P>
